<p>Leaving Colombo we hugged the Indian coast for a couple of days &amp; cut across the Arabian sea.<br/>The heat was terriffic at Aden. We were promised leave ashore here but when arrived we were told of a Smallpox outbreak so after staying half a day we left. The natives here again are great dealers curios &amp; eatables &amp; Tobacco.<br/>Saw a red headed nigger.<br/><strike>Arrived Suez</strike> There is a big army garrison at Aden. It is said that rain falls about once in seven years.<br/>Arrived Suez.  April 1<br/>We the red sea is so called</p>
